                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d682">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/2121: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-10-21T11:00:00+07:00"
                            >October 21, 1938—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:42 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>509. [Following to Canton:] Your October 18, 4 p.m.<note n="23" xml:id="d682fn23"
                        >Not printed.</note> I am separately repeating to you Department’s 271
                    October 19, 7 p.m. to me. It is my considered opinion that it would be unwise to
                    post a sentry as planned at the gate of the Hackett [Memorial] Hospital. Such
                    naval force as you have should be used for the protection of American lives and
                    American interests and you should state in explaining reason for withdrawal of
                    such sentry that this is your reason.</p>
                <p>Sent to Canton.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
